<title>Copyright</title>
<body background="../cbcbg01.gif">
<center>
<img src="../whob22t.gif">

<H1>Copyright</H1>
<hr>
</center>

All rights in the documentation of the WHO Regional Office for Europe (WHO/Europe) are reserved. WHO documentation enjoys copyright protection in accordance with the provisions of protocol 2 of the Universal Copyright Convention. The WHO name and emblem are protected and may not be used on any translation or reproduction without permission.

<H2>Publications</H2>
Neither books nor any parts of them (<a href="../docpub/prelim.htm"><B>see catalogue</B></A>) may be reproduced or transmitted in any form or by any means, electronic or mechanical, including photocopying, microfilming and recording, or by any information storage or retrieval system, without prior permission in writing from the copyright holder. Nevertheless, WHO/Europe welcomes requests for permission to translate or reproduce its publications, in part or in full. <p>


WHO/Europe is glad to provide the latest information on plans for new editions and reprints and translations already available.
<H2>Documents</H2>
Documents of WHO/Europe may be freely reviewed, abstracted, reproduced or translated, but not for sale or in conjunction with commercial purposes. WHO/Europe appreciates receiving three copies of any translation.
<h2>Applications and inquiries</h2>

Office of Publications<br>
WHO Regional Office for Europe<br>
Scherfigsvej 8<br>
DK-2100 Copenhagen <br>
Denmark
<p>
(or <a href=mailto:gni@who.dk><B>send e-mail</B></A> to gni@who.dk).




