<h1 align=center>Networks</h1>

<HR>

Improving health throughout the European Region is too big a job for any one organization. So WHO/Europe carries out its work with a wide variety of partners: individuals, groups and organizations within and outside governments, and in different sectors and levels of activity. WHO/Europe's networks form a special category of partner. They are dedicated to particular goals - such as creating healthy cities or reducing chronic disease - and pursue them through formal structures and statements of purpose. Networks are vital partners in the work for health for all.

<hr>
<center>
<table>
<tr><td><img src="../whoblk.gif"></td><td>  &copy; WHO Regional Office for Europe<BR>
<font size=2>URL: http://www.who.dk/</font><BR>
<font size=2><i>Updated 30 September 1996 - jfr@who.dk</i></font></td></tr>
</table>


