<center>
<H1>Policy statements</H1>
<HR>
</center>

At WHO conferences, the Member States of the European Region issue statements addressing important areas of the health for all policy.

<h4>
<UL>
<LI><a href="ottawa.htm">Ottawa Charter for Health Promotion, 1986</A>
<LI><a href="vienna.htm">Vienna Declaration on Nursing in Support of the European Targets for Health for All, 1988</A>
<LI><a href="tobacco.htm">The Charter Against Tobacco, 1988</A>
<LI><a href="ehchart.htm">European Charter on Environment and Health, 1989</A>
<li><a href="milan01.htm">The Milan Declaration on Healthy Cities, 1990</A>


<LI><a href="women.htm">Vienna Statement on Investing in Women's Health in the Countries of Central and Eastern Europe,1994</A>
<li><a href="helsinki.htm">Declaration on Action for Environment and Health in Europe, 1994</A>

<LI><a href="copenh.htm">The Copenhagen Declaration on Health Policy, 1994</A>
<LI><a href="alcohol.htm">European Charter on Alcohol, 1995</A>
<li>The Ljubljana Charter on Reforming Health Care<br>
<a href="../cpa/charter.htm">In English</A>  <a href="../cpa/chart-f.htm">In French</A>  <a href="../cpa/chart-g.htm">In German</A>
</UL>
</h4>

