<a href="tpeh.htm"><img src="../nextknap.gif"></A>



<center>
<h1>Health Promotion <br>and Disease Prevention</h1>

<HR>
</center>
The Health Promotion and Disease Prevention Department helps countries promote health by advocating healthy living and settings conducive to it, and action against harmful substances. It also spearheads action to prevent and control diseases and accidents.
<p>
Its technical programmes are:
<h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="./hp/hp01.htm">Investment in Health and Noncommunicable Disease Prevention</A>
<li><a href="./hp/hp02.htm">Lifestyles and Health</A>
<li><a href="./hp/hp03.htm">Sexual and Family Health</A>
<li><a href="./hp/hp04.htm">Communicable Diseases</A>
</ul>
</h4>
<hr>
<center>
<table>
<tr><td><img src="../whoblk.gif"></td><td>   WHO Regional Office for Europe<BR>
<font size=2>URL: http://www.who.dk/</font><BR>
<font size=2><i>Updated 12 August 1996 - jfr@who.dk</i></font></td></tr>
</table>
