<title>Health Policy and Services</title>
<body background="../cbcbg01.gif">
<img src="techhead.gif">
<br>
<a href="../Welcome.htm"><img src="../homeknap.gif"></A>
<a href="tech.htm"><img src="../sectknap.gif"></A>
<a href="tpeh.htm"><img src="../prevknap.gif"></a>
<a href="tpch.htm"><img src="../nextknap.gif"></A>
<center>
<H1>Health Policy and Services</H1>
<hr>
</center>

The Health Policy and Services Department helps Member States, particularly the CCEE, refom their health care systems. It supports the making of health policy and its implementation in three closely related areas: services, how they are delivered and the people who provide them.
<p>
Its technical programmes are:
<h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="./hs/hs01.htm">Health Policy</A>
<li><a href="./hs/hs02.htm">Health Care Systems</A>
<li><a href="./hs/hs03.htm">Health Care Delivery</A>
<li><a href="./hs/hs04.htm">Human Resources Development</A>
</ul>
</h4>

<hr>
<center>
<table>
<tr><td><img src="../whoblk.gif"></td><td>   WHO Regional Office for Europe<BR>
<font size=2>URL: http://www.who.dk/</font><BR>
<font size=2><i>Updated 12 August 1996 - jfr@who.dk</i></font></td></tr>
</table>
</html>

