<html>
<title>Country Health Development</title>
<body background="../cbcbg01.gif">
<img src="techhead.gif">
<br>
<a href="../Welcome.htm"><img src="../homeknap.gif"></A>
<a href="tech.htm"><img src="../sectknap.gif"></A>
<a href="tech.htm"><img src="../prevknap.gif"></A>
<center>
<H1>Country Health Development</H1>
<hr>
</center>
The Country Health Development Department manages WHO/Europe's activities in countries, particularly in the CCEE and NIS. It focuses on gathering and reporting data on health, improving the quality of care, coordinating WHO/Europe's work with that of other organizations and delivering humanitarian assistance.
<p>


Its technical programmes are:

<h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="./ch/ch01.htm">EUROHEALTH</A>
<li><a href="./ch/ch02.htm">Coordination and Humanitarian Assistance</A>
<li><a href="./ch/ch03.htm">Epidemiology, Statistics and Health Information</A>
<li><a href="./ch/ch04.htm">Quality of Care and Pharmaceuticals</A>
</ul>

</h4>



<hr>
<center>
<table>
<tr><td><img src="../whoblk.gif"></td><td>   WHO Regional Office for Europe<BR>
<font size=2>URL: http://www.who.dk/</font><BR>
<font size=2><i>Updated 12 August 1996 - jfr@who.dk</i></font></td></tr>
</table>
