<center>
<H2>Health for all<BR>
statistical database (HFA/PC)<BR>
for MS DOS </H2>

<H3>Updated February 1997 </H3>

<H3>(Provisional updating) </H3>
<hr>
</center>

This package contains data on selected health statistics for European
countries, called Health for All Indicators, and includes software
to display these data in a user-friendly way. Full list of indicators
of this package can be exported as a text file and printed whenever
needed (see Help text). The World Health Organization, Regional
Office for Europe, collects data from various sources, primarily
from national counterparts on health statistics. The main sources
of information are listed in the file SOURCES.HFA. The database
is periodically updated, as more recent data become available.
<P>
The HFAP/PC can be downloaded from Internet by:
<H3>1) Using FTP: </H3>

<UL>
<LI>Connect to ftp.who.dk
<LI>Use ANONYMOUS as userid and your own Internet ID as password

<LI>Choose files from the library /IN or /HFA
<LI>The files SETHFAD.EXE and README.DOS contain the DOS version

<LI>The files SETHFAW.EXE and README.WIN contain the Windows'
version
<LI>Switch to binary mode before receiving the .EXE files.
</UL>

<H3>2) Via WWW </H3>

<UL>
<LI>Connect to home page of WHO/EURO's World-Wide Web Server (http://www.who.dk)
<LI>Select &quot;Country Information&quot;
<LI>Download instructions and HFA data base.
</UL>

<P>
Requests for copies of the HFA/PC (both DOS and WINDOWS versions)
can also be forwarded to:
<P>
ADR/DIS unit, WHO Regional Office for Europe, Scherfigsvej 8, DK-2100
Copenhagen, Telefax: +45 39 17 18 18
<P>
Copies can also be obtained from the WHO documentation centres
that have been established in a number of countries. Please note
that the Regional Office may charge a certain amount to cover
the cost of the diskette and handling expenses.
<P>
The HFA/PC package may be copied for use by other individual users
or organizations, under the condition that it is not used for
commercial purposes and this README.1st file is also copied without
change.
<H3>Disclaimer </H3>


Users should note that the data for some indicators have been
obtained from various sources, and that the comparability of these
indicators between countries is limited, owing to differences
in the definitions and measurement practices used in different
countries and/or time periods. Some of historical mortality data
for before 1990 for the former USSR have been received via technical
collaboration with the institutions possessing these data and
cannot be seen as official data provided to WHO by the Member
States concerned. Any changes in the data that may subsequently
be received from new Member States will be included in later versions
of the package.
<P>
The maps presented here do not imply the expression of any opinion
whatsoever on the part of the Secretariat of the World Health
Organization concerning the legal status of any country, territory,
city or area or of its authorities, or concerning the delimitation
of its frontiers or boundaries.
<P>
In no event shall WHO or its collaborating centres be responsible
for any incidental or consequential damages or losses caused by
the use of the HFA/PC package.
<H3>Installation </H3>

<P>
To run the HFA/PC (version for MS DOS 5 or higher), your PC will
require about 520 Mbytes free RAM and about 5 Mbytes free space
on hard disk. The system requires VGA mode and installed mouse.
<P>
1. Create a directory on your hard disk and copy all files from
the distribution diskette (or ones downloaded from Internet) into
the new directory. You can do this with the following MS DOS commands:
<P>
C:&gt; MD HFADOS97
<BR>
C:&gt; CD HFADOS97
<BR>
C:\HFADOS97&gt; COPY A:\*.*
<P>
or COPY B:\*.*
<P>
2. Then run the SETHFAD.EXE to decompress data files:
<P>
C:\HFADOS97&gt; SETHFAD
<P>
3. After installation you may wish to delete SETHFAD.EXE to save
space.
<P>
4. To run the program type:
<P>
C:\HFADOS97&gt; HFA
<P>
Read Help text first. From Parameters menu select up to five indicators,
countries and years which you are intertested in. Select any graphical
or tabular data disply option to disply this data.
<H3>Contact </H3>

<P>
Please report any problems or noticed inaccuracies in data to:
<P>
Epidemiology, Statistics and Health Information unit <BR>Attn. Dr.R.Prokhorskas<BR>
WHO Regional Office for Europe <BR>Scherfigsvej 8 <BR>DK-2100 Copenhagen<BR>
Tel: (45) 39 17 14 82 or (45) 39 17 14 39 <BR>Fax: (45) 39 17 18<BR>
95 E-mail (Internet): <a href=mailto:RPR@WHO.DK>RPR@WHO.DK</A>
<P>
Any comments and suggestions for improvements of this package
would be also very much appreciated.

<hr>
