<center>

<H1>Acknowledgement</H1>
<br clear=left>
<hr>
</center>

<P>
This report has been produced by the Communication and Public
Affairs Unit (CPA) of the WHO Regional Office for Europe through
a "bottom-up process". Its theme and structure were
developed by field office heads and public information staff in
a communications workshop held in January 1996 in Sarajevo. Special
representatives and field office staff wrote draft sections. Margaret
Buter, Public Information Coordinator, Zagreb, reviewed and compiled
these contributions. Gregory Hess, of the WHO Coordination and
Humanitarian Assistance Unit in Copenhagen, along with CPA, edited
these. Fradley Garner, writer, spun the first edited version into
a cohesive whole. The draft was then reviewed by WHO's executive
management and special representatives. CPA integrated their comments.
Mary Stewart Burgher, of the WHO Publications Unit in the Regional
Office, did a final editing.
<P>
Frederik Hardvendel of Cross-Border Communications, Denmark, has
been the art director throughout as well as a contributor of some
photographs. S&oslash;ren Svensen, photographer, generously donated
photographs to illustrate the manuscript. Mich&egrave;le Whyte,
Peter Savage, Adam Norris, Rick Bayles, and Steve Turner of Worldwide
Television News have produced the video version of this report.
<P>
Thanks are due to both named and other contributors. We hope our
field staff can see themselves in this report, although for the
most part their pictures do not appear. We hope our donors will
get a better feel for the work WHO does, and that this report
will lead to greater support for the people of Bosnia and Herzegovina,
Croatia, and the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (Serbia and Montenegro)
as they cross the bridge to peace.
<P>
<I>Annette Andkjaer</I> and <I>Franklin Apfel</I>
<P>
Communication and Public Affairs
<P>
WHO Regional Office for Europe<BR>

