<IMG SRC="ismslog3.gif" align=left>


<H1><CENTER>Overview</CENTER>
</H1>

<br clear=left>
<HR>


Information on this page has been selected from the ISMS reports
which can be obtained <A href=mailto:mha@who.dk><b>via E-mail from the ISMS office.</b></A>

<h4>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#Vaccine">Vaccines</A>

<LI><A HREF="#Drugs" >Life saving drugs</A>

<LI><A HREF="#Medicalequipment">Basic medical equipment</A>

<LI><A HREF="ismsmain.htm">Return to the ISMS Main menu</A>

</UL>

</h4>
<HR>

<H2><a name="Vaccine">Vaccines</A></H2>

<H3>Quarterly reports on vaccine needs and supplies in the NIS
</H3>

Quarterly reports on vaccine needs and supplies in the NIS include the following:
<ul>
<LI>Quarterly summary overview reports on vaccine needs
and supplies in the NIS.
<br>
These reports provide a summary presentation on the comparative
status of vaccine needs and supplies among the NIS countries.

<UL>
<LI>Annual needs for primary immunization estimated by the
NIS Ministries of Health and by WHO/EURO.
<LI>Annual needs for non-primary immunization estimated by
NIS Ministries of Health and by WHO/EURO.
<LI>Extra needs for emergencies estimated by the NIS Ministries
of Health and by WHO/EURO.
<LI>Purchases and donations delivered or planned to be delivered
to the NIS
<LI>Stocks
</UL>

<LI>Quarterly follow-up country reports on the status of
vaccine needs and supplies in each of the NIS (14).

<br>
These reports contain a wealth of information on each NIS
country's:

<UL>
<LI>Projections of needs
<LI>Production
<LI>Purchases and donations delivered or planned to be delivered</I>
<LI>Stocks
<LI>National immunization schedules
<LI>Incidence of selected vaccine preventable diseases
<LI>Immunization coverage
<LI>Vaccine administrations.

</UL>

</UL>


<HR>

<H3>Highlights on vaccine needs and supplies in the NIS
</H3>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="vaccin95.htm"><h4>Overview on vaccine needs and supplies 1995</h4></A>


<LI>A quick glance to some of the latest information on vaccine
needs and supplies in the NIS. Taken from the most recent
ISMS quarterly report<IMG SRC="construc.gif">
(Data is still being collected)

</UL>

<HR>

<H2><a name="Drugs">Lifesaving drugs</A></H2>

<UL>

<li>Quarterly reports on life saving drugs needs and supplies in the NIS include the
following:

<UL>
<LI>Quarterly summary overview report on drug needs in the
NIS.<BR>
These reports provide comparative data on the status of life
saving drugs needs among the NIS.



<LI>Quarterly follow-up country reports on the status of
drug needs in each of the NIS (10).<BR>
These reports contain a wealth of information on:

<UL>
<LI>Annual needs
<LI>Purchases and donations delivered or planned to be delivered
<LI>Stocks
<LI>Production
<LI>Mortality incidence linked to the main causes of death
in each of the NIS.
</UL>

<LI>Highlights on
life saving drugs needs and supplies in the NIS

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="drugs95.htm" ><h4>Overview on drug needs 1995</h4></A>

<LI>A quick glance to some of the latest information on life
saving drugs needs and supplies in the NIS. Taken from the
most recent ISMS quarterly report <IMG SRC="construc.gif">
(Data is still being collected)
</UL>
</ul>
</ul>

<HR>

<H2><A NAME="Medicalequipment">Basic medical equipment</A><BR>
</H2>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="equipm95.htm" ><h4>Overview on basic medical equipment needs 1995</h4></A>
<BR>

<LI>1996 Overview on equipment needs <IMG SRC="construc.gif">
(Data is still being collected) <BR>

</UL>


