<TITLE>Ten reasons why not!</TITLE>

<BODY BACKGROUND="backgrnd.gif">
<P>
<A NAME="Top"><IMG SRC="../techhead.gif" ALT="Technical programmes" HEIGHT="87" WIDTH="472">
<BR>
</A><A HREF="../../Welcome.htm"><IMG SRC="../../homeknap.gif" height=20 width=110 border=0></A>
<A href="../tech.htm"><IMG src="../../sectknap.gif" height=20 width=110 border=0></A>
<A href="index.htm"><IMG src="../../prevknap.gif" height=20 width=110 border=0></A>
<A href="index.htm"><IMG src="../../nextknap.gif" height=20 width=110 border=0></A>
<H1><CENTER><IMG SRC=" hcpsmall.gif" ALT="Healthy City small logo" WIDTH="147" HEIGHT="104" ALIGN="LEFT">Ten
reasons why not! </CENTER></H1>

<P>
<BR clear=left>

<HR>

<P>
Return to <A HREF="index.htm">WHO Healthy Cities homepage</A>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG src="byline.gif" height=13 width=13> </CENTER>
<H2><CENTER>Ten reasons why Healthy Cities is NOT appropriate
for your city! </CENTER></H2>

<OL>
<LI>You think that the implementation of health for all should
be the exclusive responsibility of national governments.
<LI>You think that health is mainly the responsibility of doctors
and nurses.
<LI>You feel that health for all and sustainable development is
too theoretical and irrelevant to your needs.
<LI>You believe in top-down hierarchical management.
<LI>You feel that experts know best what is good for your citizens.
<LI>You feel that Healthy Cities is a luxury and a project for
rich cities only.
<LI>You think that international cooperation is a waste of time.
<LI>You do not want to be different.
<LI>You believe that investing in long-term projects will not
get you re-elected.
<LI>You are too busy.
</OL>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG src="byline.gif" height=13 width=13> </CENTER>
<H2><CENTER>Click <A HREF="contacts.htm">here</A> for contact
information. </CENTER></H2>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG src="byline.gif" height=13 width=13> </CENTER>
<P>
<A HREF="#Top">Return to top</A>
<HR>
</TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER>
