<H1><CENTER><IMG SRC=" hcpsmall.gif" ALT="Healthy City small logo" WIDTH="147" HEIGHT="104" ALIGN="LEFT">WHO
collaborating centres for healthy cities </CENTER></H1>

<P>
<BR clear=left>
<HR>

<P>
Return to <A HREF="index.htm">WHO Healthy Cities homepage</A>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG src="byline.gif" height=13 width=13> </CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><I><FONT COLOR=#000080>Save or print this page for reference</FONT></I></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>This page lists those WHO collaborating centres for healthy
cities who have work plans with the <A HREF="/Welcome.html">WHO Regional Office for Europe</A>,
Healthy Cities Project Office.</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><A NAME="Top"><IMG src="byline.gif" height=13 width=13>
</A></CENTER>
<DL>
<DT><IMG SRC="blueb01.gif" height=14 width=14 ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0">
<A HREF="#Nottingham">WHO collaborating centre for healthy cities and primary health care</A>
(Nottingham)
<DT><IMG SRC="blueb01.gif" height=14 width=14 ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0">
<A HREF="#Indiana">WHO collaborating centre for healthy cities</A>
(Indiana)
<DT><IMG SRC="blueb01.gif" height=14 width=14 ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0">
<A HREF="#Maastricht">WHO collaborating centre for research on healthy cities</A>
(Maastricht)
<DT><IMG SRC="blueb01.gif" height=14 width=14 ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0">
<A HREF="#Rennes">Centre collaborateur de l'OMS sur les villes sant&eacute;</A>
(Rennes)
</DL>

<P>
<CENTER><A NAME="Nottingham"><IMG src="byline.gif" height=13 width=13>
</A></CENTER>
<H2><CENTER><A HREF="http://www.ccc.nottingham.ac.uk/~mhzwww/sph/intro.html"><IMG SRC="nottsph.gif" height=84 width=66 ALIGN="left"></A>
WHO collaborating centre for healthy cities and primary health
care </CENTER></H2>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="http://www.ccc.nottingham.ac.uk/~mhzwww/sph/intro.html">http://www.ccc.nottingham.ac.uk/~mhzwww/sph/intro.html</A></CENTER>
<P>
<A HREF="#Top">Return to top</A>
<P>
The centre is based in the School of Public Health in the University
of Nottingham. It serves as a resource centre for the WHO Healthy
Cities Project Office for public health and health services development
in countries of central, eastern and southern Europe.
<P>
Director:<BR>
Professor Richard J. Madeley<BR>
Nottingham School of Public Health<BR>
Queen's Medical Center<BR>
Nottingham NG7 2UH<BR>
United Kingdom
<P>
Tel : +44 (0115) 970 9313<BR>
Fax : +44 (0115) 970 9316<BR>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:sph@nottingham.ac.uk">sph@nottingham.ac.uk</A>
<P>
<CENTER><A NAME="Indiana"><IMG src="byline.gif" height=13 width=13>
</A></CENTER>
<H2><CENTER><A HREF="http://indyunix.iupui.edu/~citynet/iarch.html"><IMG SRC="iarch.gif" height=67 width=121 ALIGN="left"></A>
WHO collaborating centre for healthy cities </CENTER></H2>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="http://indyunix.iupui.edu/~citynet/iarch.html">http://indyunix.iupui.edu/~citynet/iarch.html</A></CENTER>
<P>
<A HREF="#Top">Return to top</A>
<P>
The centre is based in the Institute of Action Research for Community
Health (IARCH), which was established in June 1990 at the Indiana
University School of Nursing with the following purposes:
<UL>
<LI>to promote, develop and conduct interdisciplinary research
relevant to community health issues in the state, the nation and
the world;
<LI>to provide new opportunities for community health research,
public service, and education for students and faculty;
<LI>to collaborate with communities in identifying solutions to
their health concerns.
</UL>

<P>
Director:<BR>
Dr Beverly C. Flynn<BR>
Head, WHO collaborating centre in healthy cities<BR>
Indiana University School of Nursing<BR>
Nursing 236<BR>
1111 Middle Drive<BR>
Indianapolis<BR>
IN 46202-5107<BR>
USA
<P>
Tel: +1 317 274 3319<BR>
Fax: +1 317 274 2285<BR>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:citynet@indyvax.iupui.edu">citynet@indyvax.iupui.edu</A>
<P>
