<H1 align=center>Genetic Services</H1>
<hr>
<H2>Community genetics services in
Europe</H2>
<H3>Report on a survey</H3>

By B. Modell, A.M. Kuliev and M. Wagner<BR>
WHO Regional Publications,<BR>
European Series, No. 38<BR>
1991, x + 137 pages [E, F, G]<BR>
ISBN 92 890 1301 X<BR>
Sw.fr. 24.-<BR>
Order No. 1310038<P>
<P>
Explains the kinds of genetic disorders that exist and assesses their social and ethical
implications; reviews existing community genetics services in Europe (use of primary
prevention, neonatal screening, and prevention of congenital malformations,
chromosomal abnormalities and inherited disease) and the limitations of prenatal
diagnosis; and expounds the way such services should develop in the future.<P>
