<HR>
<H3>Helpers in childbirth: midwifery today</H3>
By Ann Oakley and Susanne Houd<BR>
1990, 203 pages<BR>
ISBN 1 56032 036 2<BR>
ISSN 1047 4005<BR>
US $35.-<P>

Brings to the forefront a key issue: the role of midwives in maternity care today. The
authors - a sociologist and a practising midwife - trace midwifery through history and
explain how this form of childbirth has become an alternative rather than the official
approach in western culture. They describe the legal aspects, the education and training
needed, and the practice of midwifery in various countries. The book also describes the
growing consumer protest in favour of midwifery. The book includes moving and
informative transcripts from actual birth scenes. Illustrated with black-and-white
photographs.
