<HR>
<H2>Published by Monduzzi Editore</H2>
<H3>HIV and AIDS-related suicidal behaviour </H3>
<H4>Report on a WHO consultation</H4>

Edited by Jan E. Beskow, Maurizio Bellini, Jos G. Sampaio Faria and Ad J.F.M.
Kerkhof<P>

1991, 76 pages<BR>
ISBN 88 323 1753 6<P>

Suicides are on the increase in the European Region. With the development of the AIDS
epidemic, an additional large group of people at risk of depression and suicidal behaviour
has emerged. This book is the result of a consultation of experts called by the WHO
Regional Office for Europe to assess the real likelihood of people with HIV and AIDS
resorting to suicide. It presents case studies from Finland, Germany, Italy, the
Netherlands, Sweden, a review of the American literature and a report on research into
clinical and ethical aspects of deliberate self-harm in people with HIV.<P>
