<HTML>
<TITLE>Resolutions 1984</TITLE>

<body background="../cbcbg01.gif">




<img src="abouhead.gif">
<br>

<a href="../Welcome.htm"><img src="../homeknap.gif"></A>
<a href="about.htm"><img src="../sectknap.gif"></A> 
<a href="resolu.htm"><img src="../prevknap.gif"></A> 
<a href="resolu35.htm"><img src="../nextknap.gif"></A> 














<H1 align=center>Resolutions 1984</H1>
<HR>

<H2>Resolution EUR/RC34/R1</H2>

<H2>Nomination of the Regional Director</H2>
<UL>
<LI>The Regional Committee for Europe,
</LI>
<LI>Considering Article 52 of the Constitution;
</LI>
<LI>In accordance with Rule 47 of its Rules of Procedure;
</LI>
</UL><OL>
<LI>NOMINATES Dr J.E. Asvall as Regional Director for Europe;
</LI>
<LI>REQUESTS the Director-General to propose to the Executive Board the
appointment of Dr J.E. Asvall for a  period of five years from 1
February 1985.
</LI>
</OL><HR>




<H2>Resolution EUR/RC34/R2</H2>
<H2>Vote of thanks to Dr Leo A. Kaprio</H2>
<UL>
<LI>The Regional Committee,
</LI>
<LI>Considering the outstanding services rendered to international
public health by Dr Kaprio during his years of  service with the World
Health Organization, and particularly during his 18 years as Regional
Director for Europe;
</LI>
<LI>Believing that when he ceases his duties on 31 January 1985, his
contribution to improving the health of people  throughout the European
Region deserves particular appreciation on the part of the World Health
Organization and its  Member States;
</LI>
</UL><OL>
<LI>EXPRESSES its sincere thanks;
</LI>
<LI>DECLARES Dr Leo A. Kaprio Regional Director Emeritus of the World
Health Organization.
</LI>
</OL><HR>



<H2>Resolution EUR/RC34/R3</H2>
<H2>Annual report of the Regional Director</H2>
<UL>
<LI>The Regional Committee,
</LI>
<LI>Having reviewed the report on the work of WHO in the European
Region in 1983;
</LI>
</UL><OL>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director for his report;
</LI>
<LI>EXPRESSES its satisfaction with the work accomplished by the
Regional Office in 1983;
</LI>
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director to take into account the suggestions
made during the discussion in the future  work of the Regional Office.
</LI>
</OL><HR>
<H2>Resolution EUR/RC34/R4</H2>
<H3>Proposed programme budget for 1986-1987 and preliminary targets for 1988-1991</H3>
<UL>
<LI>The Regional Committee,
</LI>
<LI>Having reviewed in detail the proposed programme budget for the
biennium 1986-1987;
</LI>
<LI>Having considered the comments made by the Consultative Group on
Programme Development and the  Consultative Group on Budgetary
Questions;
</LI>
</UL><OL>
<LI>WELCOMES the modified presentation of the document, whereby the
information formerly contained in part II  has been integrated into the
body of the document, and the inclusion of additional information on
country  programmes;
</LI>
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director, during implementation of the
programme, to take into account the views  expressed during the
discussions at the Regional Committee and in particular:
<OL>
<LI>to give priority to activities in support of the regional targets
for health for all and, where necessary, to make the  corresponding
adjustments to the budgetary allocations;
</LI>
<LI>to ensure the efficient and economic use of all available
resources;
</LI>
<LI>to step up efforts to raise extrabudgetary resources in support of
programme development;
</LI>
</OL></LI>
<LI>ENDORSES, on this basis, the proposed programme for 1986-1987, to
be financed under the regular budget  and with funds from other sources,
to the extent that they become available;
</LI>
<LI>RECOMMENDS, on the same basis, its inclusion in the
Director-General's proposed programme budget for the  Organization in
1986-1987.
</LI>
</OL><HR>



<H2>Resolution EUR/RC34/R5</H2>
<H2>Implementation of the regional strategy for attaining health for all by the year 2000: European regional targets</H2>
<UL>
<LI>The Regional Committee,
</LI>
<LI>Bearing in mind resolution WHA30.43 which calls upon all countries
to collaborate in the achievement of the  goal of health for all by the
year 2000 (HFA2000) through the development of corresponding health
policies and  programmes at the national, regional and international
levels;
</LI>
<LI>Recalling resolution EUR/RC30/R8 which endorses the regional
strategy for attaining HFA2000 and  acknowledges that it should foster
the development and implementation of national health policies,
strategies and  plans of action;
</LI>
<LI>Further recalling resolution EUR/RC33/R4 which requests the
Regional Director to submit a final version of the  regional target
document to the thirty-fourth session of the Regional Committee,
together with a plan of action and a  list of indicators for monitoring
progress towards achieving the targets in the Region;
</LI>
<LI>Having considered:
<OL>
<LI>the proposed regional targets in support of the regional strategy
for health for all (EUR/RC34/7);
</LI>
<LI>the list of proposed indicators for monitoring progress towards
health for all in the European Region  (EUR/RC34/13);
</LI>
<LI>the proposed plan of action for implementation of the regional
strategy for attaining HFA2000 (EUR/RC34/14);
</LI>
<LI>the reports of the Consultative Group on Programme Development
(EUR/RC34/8 and EUR/RC34/8 Add.1), the  Regional Health Development
Advisory Council (EUR/RC34/5), and the European Advisory Committee for
Medical  Research (EUR/RC34/6);
</LI>
</OL></LI>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director, the advisory groups and the other
experts involved in the preparation of these  documents for their
valuable contributions;
</LI>
<LI>ENDORSES, for application as appropriate, having regard to the
particular circumstances of individual Member  States;
<OL>
<LI>the regional targets in support of the regional strategy for health
for all (EUR/RC34/7);
</LI>
<LI>the list of indicators for monitoring progress towards health for
all in the European Region (EUR/RC34/13) as  being preliminary only, to
be used for the first time in the 1985 evaluation - the results of which
will be discussed at  the next session of the Regional Committee - and
thereafter adjusted as necessary;
</LI>
<LI>similarly, as being preliminary only, the plan of action for
implementation of the regional strategy for HFA2000  (EUR/RC34/14);
</LI>
</OL></LI>
<LI>URGES Member States:
<OL>
<LI>to step up their efforts to establish national policies and
programmes that are in line with the regional strategy for  health for
all, and to set national targets in such a way that they also contribute
to attainment of the regional targets;
</LI>
<LI>(b)  to give special emphasis, when so doing, to the managerial
processes and structures required to support  national developments
towards health for all, and to information systems in order to ensure
coverage of the lists of  global and essential regional indicators as
far as possible;
</LI>
<LI>when reporting to the Regional Director, as far as possible to
provide all the necessary information on progress  and effectiveness in
implementing their strategies for health for all, and in particular data
related to the global and  essential regional indicators, as reflected
in the plan of action and by resolution WHA35.23;
</LI>
<LI>to seek cooperation as and when required for these purposes;
</LI>
</OL></LI>
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>to transmit these documents, amended where necessary to take
account of constitutional matters in particular  Member States, together
with the minutes of the Regional Committee, to the Director-General as a
European regional  contribution to attainment of the global target of
health for all;
</LI>
<LI>to give priority, in the programme of work and budget allocations
of the WHO Regional Office for Europe, to  activities designed to
provide Member States with adequate support in working out national
strategies for health for  all, as well as to those developments in the
Region as a whole which may facilitate attainment of the regional
targets;
</LI>
<LI>to report to the Regional Committee in accordance with the plan of
action.
</LI>
</OL></LI>
</UL><HR>
<H2>Resolution EUR/RC34/R6</H2>
<H2>Technical discussions and visits at future sessions of the Regional Committee</H2>
<UL>
<LI>The Regional Committee,
</LI>
<LI>Having considered the relevant part of the report on methods of
work of the Regional Committee for Europe  (EUR/RC34/4);
</LI>
<LI>Emphasizing the value of technical discussions and the desirability
of continuing them in the most effective  manner at future sessions of
the Regional Committee;
</LI>
<LI>Likewise stressing the practical benefit to be derived from
enabling participants in sessions of the Regional  Committee to acquaint
themselves with the health and related services of the countries where
the sessions are held;
</LI>
</UL><OL>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director for his report;
</LI>
<LI>DECIDES that:
<OL>
<LI>when sessions of the Regional Committee are held in Copenhagen (in
even years), technical discussions should  be arranged but technical
visits should not normally take place;
</LI>
<LI>when sessions of the Regional Committee are held elsewhere (in odd
years), technical discussions should not  take place, but arrangements
should be made for visits to acquaint participants with the health and
related services of  the host country;
</LI>
</OL></LI>
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>to continue to arrange for technical discussions when sessions of
the Regional Committee are held in  Copenhagen;
</LI>
<LI>not to arrange for technical discussions when sessions are held
elsewhere, but to consult and make arrangements  with the host
government for visits to enable participants to acquaint themselves with
the health and related services of  the host country.
</LI>
</OL></LI>
</OL><HR>
<H2>Resolution EUR/RC34/R7</H2>
<H2>Technical discussion at future sessions of the Regional Committee</H2>
<UL>
<LI>The Regional Committee,
</LI>
</UL><OL>
<LI>CONFIRMS that the subject of the main technical discussions at its
thirty-fifth session shall be "Infectious  diseases:  current problems
in the European Region";
</LI>
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director to make the necessary arrangements.
</LI>
</OL><HR>


<H2>Resolution EUR/RC34/R8</H2>
<H2>Date and place of regular sessions of the Regional Committee in 1985 and 1986</H2>
<UL>
<LI>The Regional Committee,
</LI>
<LI>Having reviewed the decision taken at its thirty-third session;
</LI>
</UL><OL>
<LI>CONFIRMS that the thirty-fifth session shall be held in Rotterdam,
the Netherlands, from 17 to 21 September  1985;
</LI>
<LI>DECIDES that the thirty-sixth session shall be convened at the
regional headquarters in Copenhagen in  September/October 1986 for a
period not exceeding five days.
</LI>
</OL>

<hr>
