<H1 align=center>Resolutions 1993</H1>
<HR>





<H2>Resolution no. EUR/RC43/R1</H2>
<H2>Standing Committee of the Regional Committee

</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having studied the report of the Interim Standing Committee of the Regional Committee
(documents EUR/RC43/2 and /2 Add. 1) and the proposals and recommendations contained therein, which
are in accordance with Article 49 of the Constitution of WHO and the Rules of Procedure of the Regional
Committee for Europe;
<LI>	Recalling the discussions at its forty-second session on the reports of the Ad Hoc Committee on
Future Orientations of the Regional Organization (documents EUR/RC42/4 and /Inf.Doc./1) and the
resolution on Mobilization for Health (EUR/RC42/R5);
<LI>	Mindful of the magnitude of the continuing change in Europe and its consequences for the health
of the peoples of the Region and the effective operation of the Regional Organization;
<LI>	Welcoming the conclusions and recommendations of the Executive Board Working Group on
Global Change and noting with satisfaction their consistency with the general thrust of the changes already
being introduced into the European Regional Organization;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>THANKS the Interim Standing Committee of the Regional Committee for its excellent work, building
on the work of the Ad Hoc Committee;
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director and staff for their work in assisting the Interim Standing Committee;
<LI>ENDORSES the conclusions and proposals of the Interim Standing Committee, as amended during the
discussions at the forty-third session of the Regional Committee;
<LI>ADOPTS the proposed changes to the Regional Committee's Rules of Procedure and the Rules of
Procedure for the Standing Committee of the Regional Committee as amended by the Regional Committee
at its forty-third session;
<LI>	REQUESTS the Regional Director, together with officers of the Regional Committee, taking into
account the advice of the Standing Committee, to sustain efforts to ensure continued success in the
rapprochement with other organizations operating in the health sector in the European Region of WHO;
<LI>URGES all Member States to continue to support the rapprochement strategy, in order to maximize the
collective support provided by all international organizations operating in the health field in Europe.
</OL>
<HR>






<H2>Resolution no. EUR/RC43/R2</H2>
<H2>Minutes of the Regional Committee
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having considered document EUR/RC43/7 on the minutes of the Regional Committee and
recognizing the financial implications of producing written minutes of the sessions of the Regional
Committee;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>	DECIDES that:
<OL>
<LI>the written minutes of the Regional Committee shall be replaced by sound recordings;
<LI>	recordings of the whole or part of the session shall be made available to Member States on request
in the original language of the speakers and/or the interpretation into any of the four working languages of
the Region;
<LI>	a written index of speakers at each meeting shall be made and attached to each recording, in order
to facilitate location of specific items;
<LI>	transcripts of specific parts of the session shall likewise be made available on request.
</OL>
<LI>	DECIDES that Rule 18 of the Rules of Procedure of the Regional Committee for Europe shall be
amended accordingly, to read as follows.<br> "<I>Rule 18</I><br> A draft report of each session of the Regional
Committee shall be prepared by the secretariat for adoption by the Regional Committee prior to the close of
each session. The secretariat shall also arrange for sound recordings to be made of the meetings of the
Regional Committee. Such recordings of the whole or part of the session shall be made available to Member
States on request, in the original language of the speakers and/or the interpretation into any of the four
working languages of the Region. Transcripts of specific parts of sessions shall likewise be made available
upon request."
</OL>
<HR>








<H2>Resolution no. EUR/RC43/R3</H2>
<H2>Regional contribution to the Ninth General Prpogramme of Work
 (1996-2001)</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having considered document EUR/RC43/3 on the regional contribution to the Ninth General
Programme of Work (19962001);
<LI>	Noting the main thrusts of the updated health policy for Europe and its 38 targets;
<LI>	Conscious that the rapidly changing environment in the European Region requires a flexible
programme response and regional adaptation of programme classification;
<LI>	Recalling the discussions and recommendations at the forty-first and forty-second sessions of the
Regional Committee concerning the regional evaluation of progress towards health for all by the year 2000,
the updating of the health policy for Europe, and the report of the Ad Hoc Committee on the Future
Orientations of the European Regional Organization of WHO in a Changing Europe;
<LI>	Welcoming the proposal to shorten the planning cycle by including programme priorities and
expected future developments in the programme budget document and thus submitting only one integrated
document to the Regional Committee;
<LI>	Noting with satisfaction the proposed involvement of the Standing Committee of the Regional
Committee in the Regional Office's work on programme planning and evaluation;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>ENDORSES document EUR/RC43/3 as a basis for the European contribution to the Ninth General
Programme of Work;
<LI>	REQUESTS the Standing Committee of the Regional Committee to present its views on
programme planning and evaluation to the Regional Committee at its forty-fourth session;
<LI>	REQUESTS the Regional Director to intensify efforts to follow up and implement the
recommendations contained in document EUR/RC43/Inf.Doc./5, Report of the Executive Board Working
Group on the WHO Response to Global Change, and in resolution WHA46.35 on budgetary reform;
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director to transmit document EUR/RC43/3 and the Committee's comments
to the Director-General for his consideration in his finalization of the Ninth General Programme of Work.
</OL>
<HR>





<H2>Resolution no. EUR/RC43/R4</H2>
<H2>Report of the Executive Board working group on the WHO response to global change
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Recalling resolutions WHA46.16, WHA46.35, EB92/R2 and EUR/RC42/R5,
<LI>	Having studied the report of the Executive Board Working Group on the WHO Response to
Global Change and the Regional Director's comments on the Report (EUR/RC43/6, Part II);
<LI>	Welcoming all efforts to improve the effectiveness, efficiency and responsiveness of the whole
Organization and to facilitate dialogue and consensus among its various levels;
<LI>	Noting the relevance of the Working Group's analysis and recommendations for the European
Region and its consistency with the measures already being taken by the Regional Organization;
<LI>	Conscious that the regional level plays a crucial role in the Organization by providing support to
countries and leadership in health and needs stronger funding to enable it to fulfil its responsibility;
<LI>	Convinced that any new organizational and managerial arrangements emerging from the present
reform process must satisfy the particular needs and circumstances of each region and its Member States,
and be in line with the principles of decentralization as expressed in the WHO Constitution;
<LI>	Conscious that the global health for all policy endorsed in 1977 (resolution WHA30.43), which is
an important instrument of the Organization's leadership in health, has not been adapted to global change;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director for his comments (document EUR/RC43/6,
<LI>Part II) and accepts the report, as modified in the light of the discussions and comments of the
Regional Committee, as constituting the views of the Regional Committee;
<LI>ENDORSES the steps that have already been taken and are being taken within the WHO Regional
Organization which are in keeping with the recommendations of the Working Group;
<LI>REQUESTS the Standing Committee of the Regional Committee to continue to study the issues and
developments relating to the global reform process and its implications for the European Region;
<LI>	ASKS Member States to review their present arrangements for collaboration with the Regional
Office and to take action to strengthen it as may be required;
<LI>	REQUESTS the Regional Director
<OL>
<LI>to forward the Regional Committee's views on the report of the Executive Board Working Group on
the WHO Response to Global Change to the Executive Board through the Director-General;
<LI>to report to the forty-fourth Regional Committee, as and when appropriate, on any action taken in
support of the reform process.
</OL>
<LI>	URGES the Director-General and the Executive Board to institute a process for updating the
global health for all strategy and formulating a global health for all policy with targets capable of inspiring
and guiding the Organization and its Member States beyond the year 2000.
</OL>
<HR>






<H2>Resolution no. EUR/RC43/R5</H2>
<H2>Appointment of the Regional search group
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Conscious of the constitutional role of the Regional Director in the work of the European Regional
Organization of WHO;
<LI>	Bearing in mind the recent political developments in the Region that require of the Regional
Director a high level of political sensitivity, diplomatic skills, a broad understanding of the problems of the
Region, international experience, technical competence and personal leadership skills;
<LI>	Recalling Rule 47 of the Rules of Procedure of the Regional Committee and resolution
EUR/RC40/R3, by which a clear procedure was established for ensuring the suitability of candidates;
<LI>	Having reviewed document EUR/RC43/5 on the appointment of a Regional Search Group;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>APPROVES alternative I set out in document EUR/RC43/5 regarding the appointment of a Regional
Search Group to make a preliminary evaluation of candidates for the post of Regional Director for the five-
year period starting 1 February 1995 in the light of the criteria specified by the Regional Committee and to
perform related functions as approved by resolution EUR/RC40/R3;
<LI>APPOINTS a Regional Search Group with the following members and alternates:
<PRE>
Members
			Alternates
Manciaux
		Violaki
Hyzle			Tierney
Nuri			Tonkovic
Zeltner
</PRE>
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Search Group to report on its work to the Regional Committee at its forty-
fourth session.
</OL>
<HR>




<H2>Resolution no. EUR/RC43/R6</H2>
<H2>Election of members of the Standinc Committee of the WHO regional Committee for Europe
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having considered document EUR/RC43/Inf.Doc./1 and the report of the Interim Standing
Committee of the Regional Committee, in particular regarding the composition and election of members of
the Standing Committee of the Regional Committee (SCRC);
<LI>	Noting with satisfaction the valuable work done by the interim SCRC in further elaborating the
guidelines for election of members of the SCRC, as drafted by the Ad Hoc Committee on the Future
Orientations of the European Regional Organization of WHO in a Changing Europe and submitted to the
Regional Committee at its forty-second session, together with the facilitating role played by the Regional
Director;
<LI>	Conscious of the need to select people knowledgeable and experienced in the field of public health
as members of the SCRC, in order to ensure the efficiency of the Committee while reflecting all the other
criteria for balanced membership as set out in document EUR/RC43/Inf.Doc./1;
<LI>	Having due regard to nominations received from the Member States of the European Region;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>APPOINTS the following persons as members of the SCRC for the specified terms of office, in
addition to the Deputy Executive President who is a member ex officio:
<PRE>


Chairperson:
		Zeltner (Switzerland)		1993-1994
Members:		Metters (United Kingdom)	1993-1994
			rtendahl (Sweden)
		1993-1994
			Jvor (Hungary)
			1993-1994
			Vassallo (Malta)
		1993-1995
			Girard (France)
			1993-1995
			Freire (Spain)
			1993-1995
			Koubarko (Belarus)
		1993-1996
			Alexandrov (Slovak Republic)
	1993-1996
			Prodanchuk (Ukraine)
		1993-1996
</PRE>
<LI>REQUESTS the SCRC to report back on its work to the Regional Committee at its forty-fourth
session.
</OL>
<HR>




<H2>Resolution no. EUR/RC43/R7</H2>
<H2>Date and place of regular sessions of the Regional Committee in 1994 and 1995
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having reviewed the decision taken at its forty-second session as expressed in resolution
EUR/RC42/R4;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>	CONFIRMS that the forty-fourth session shall be held at the Regional Office for Europe in
Copenhagen, from 12 to 16 September 1994;
<LI>	DECIDES that the forty-fifth session, by invitation of the Government of Israel, shall be held in
Israel from 4 to 8 September 1995.
</OL>
<HR>






<H2>Resolution no. EUR/RC43/R8</H2>
<H2>Monitoring of progress towards health for all in 1993
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Recalling resolution WHA39.7 which<I> inter alia</I> recommends a triennial periodicity for
assessment of progress towards HFA;
<LI>	Bearing in mind resolution EUR/RC4l/R5 endorsing the updating of the regional health for all
targets and indicators;
<LI>	Having considered:
<OL>
<LI>the updated regional targets and indicators in support of the regional strategy for health for all;
<LI>the 199091 evaluation of the strategy for health for all by the year 2000; a)<br>	<I>a Second evaluation of the strategy for health for all by the year 2000</I>,
Copenhagen, WHO Regional Office for Europe, 1991 (document EUR/RC4l/Inf.Doc./3).
<LI>the proposed document "Health for all monitoring for the European Region of WHO (199394)"
(EUR/RC43/12);
</OL>
</UL><OL>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director, the advisory groups and the experts involved in the preparation of
these documents for their valuable contributions;
<LI>	ENDORSES the monitoring framework and procedure, and more specifically the main changes in
the 19931994 exercise;
<LI>	URGES Member States:
<OL>
<LI>when reporting to the Regional Director, to provide all the necessary information on progress and
effectiveness in implementing their strategies for health for all, including data related to the global and
regional indicators, particularly those on equity in health, in accordance with the proposed monitoring
procedure and in resolution WHA35.23;
<LI>	to seek Regional Office support as and when required for these purposes, especially in the field of
epidemiology;
<LI>	to use HFA indicators and data in producing national HFA-oriented public health reports and to
distribute their HFA monitoring reports widely in their countries;
<LI>	to cooperate with the Regional Office in an effort to improve international reliability and
comparability of HFA data and to develop and promote common standards, definitions and instruments;
<LI>	to develop core HFA data sets, based on common standards and definitions for their countries;
</OL>
<LI>	REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>to transmit all relevant monitoring documents, together with the report of the Regional Committee, to
the Director-General as a European regional contribution to the attainment of the global strategy for health
for all;
<LI>	to collect and analyse the definitions applied by countries to any particular indicator, in order to
improve the general comparability of data;
<LI>to actively pursue with relevant bodies of the Commission of the European Communities, the
Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development, the Council of Europe, etc. a process of
harmonizing existing and planned health indicators, and to consider future cooperation with the aim of
establishing a joint European health statistics centre;
<LI>to report to the Regional Committee in accordance with the proposed monitoring procedure.
</OL>
</OL>
<HR>






<H2>Resolution no. EUR/RC43/R9</H2>
<H2>Emergency response to natural and man-made disasters in the European Region of WHO
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Conscious of WHO's constitutional obligation to furnish appropriate technical assistance and, in
emergencies, necessary aid upon the request or acceptance of governments;
<LI>	Noting the guiding principles for strengthening the coordination of humanitarian assistance of the
United Nations contained in General Assembly resolution 46/182 and resolution WHA46.6 which calls for
stronger regional mechanisms for efficient health management in emergencies;
<LI>	Recalling the specific guidance for WHO's involvement in emergency relief operations given by
the Executive Board at its ninety-first session and expressed in Executive Board resolution EB91.R10;
<LI>	Recalling the previous resolutions of the Regional Committee on natural disaster preparedness
(EUR/RC33/R5) and on health assistance to the areas and countries of former Yugoslavia (EUR/RC42/R7);
<LI>	Acknowledging the work done by the Regional Office in the areas of disaster preparedness and
emergency response and its participation in relief operations;
<LI>	Acknowledging with thanks that this work has received financial support from the European
Community and many donor countries, which reflects their appreciation for WHO's work on the ground;
<LI>	Noting with satisfaction the response of the Organization to the crisis in former Yugoslavia;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director for the information provided in document EUR/RC43/15 on
humanitarian relief operations;
<LI>	THANKS the Regional Director and his staff for the work done and for securing extrabudgetary
funds for emergency response;
<LI>	COMMENDS the staff of WHO, particularly those serving in the field, for their commitment to the
missions of WHO and the United Nations and for helping the victims of war, sometimes under conditions of
severe stress and great personal danger;
<LI>	URGES Member States:
<OL>
<LI>	to collaborate in setting up within the Regional Office a humanitarian assistance network together
with a contingency plan of action to allow swift deployment of human and material resources for WHO
humanitarian assistance work in the Region, supported by a mechanism to enable immediate funding of
such activities;
<LI>	to indicate their readiness to make available at short notice to the Regional Office, in the context of
any existing coordination work undertaken by the United Nations Department of Humanitarian Affairs,
relevant human and material health care resources and the necessary logistic support for their deployment,
in response to emergency and disaster situations;
<LI>	to facilitate the unhindered provision of humanitarian assistance through their territories;
</OL>
<LI>	REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>to undertake the reorganization of the present structure of the Regional Office and reallocation of its
resources necessary to respond rapidly to the health aspects of emergencies in the Region, so that in 1996
1997 5% of the regular budget for programme activities is used to coordinate work, raise funds and
implement activities for emergency preparedness and response;
<LI>to collaborate closely in undertaking this work with the relevant sections of the United Nations
Department of Humanitarian Affairs, to ensure that the Office's initiative complements the Department's
continuing work on improving the emergency response of the whole United Nations humanitarian system;
<LI>to examine with the Central Emergency Revolving Fund options for the establishment of a procedure
to facilitate the raising and rapid disbursement of funds for the medical aspects of humanitarian assistance
for future emergencies in the Region, such as the establishment of a subprogramme for disaster
preparedness within WHO's Voluntary Fund for Health Promotion;
<LI>to report back to the Regional Committee at its forty-fourth session.
</OL>
</OL>
<HR>





<H2>Resolution no. EUR/RC43/R10</H2>
<H2>Financing intensitied cooperation with EUROHEALTH countries
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having considered the report of the Regional Director on the EUROHEALTH programme and its
financial options (document EUR/RC43/14);
<LI>	Recalling its earlier discussions and decisions on this subject (resolutions EUR/RC40/R7,
EUR/RC41/R2 and EUR/RC42/R6);
<LI>	Acknowledging with appreciation the continuing health development efforts being made by
multilateral and bilateral agencies in their cooperation with countries of central and eastern Europe and
newly independent states (CCEE/NIS) and fully recognizing WHO's constitutional coordinating role in
international health work (as reaffirmed by resolution WHA46.6);
<LI>	Conscious that the EUROHEALTH programme resource gap of at least US $11 million confirmed
by the Regional Committee at its forty-second session is likely to widen, owing to foreseeable further
reductions in the regular budget for <BR>
19941995;
<LI>	Welcoming the initiative taken by some Member States of aligning their policies on voluntary
donations and bilateral assistance with the EUROHEALTH programme;
<LI>	Recognizing the specific situation created for the Regional Office for Europe by the increasing
number of Member States and the current economic situation;
<LI>	Noting that the share of resources allocated to the WHO regions as a whole is inadequate to take
effective action on priority health needs in the large number of countries now requiring intensified
cooperation in health in the Region;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>	THANKS the Regional Director and all the staff of the Regional Organization for their efforts to
implement and give priority to the EUROHEALTH programme;
<LI>RECOMMENDS that members of the Executive Board, as well as representatives to the World Health
Assembly, from the European Region ensure that the Region's share of global regular budget resources is
commensurate with the needs of their Member States;
<LI>	URGES Member States, in particular those with special funds for support to the CCEE/NIS, to
make contributions to the Voluntary Fund for Health Promotion  Special Account for the EUROHEALTH
programme in 19941995 and to enter into joint ventures with the Regional Organization in order to enable
its EUROHEALTH programme to operate to its full capacity;
<LI>INVITES Member States that are also members of integrational organizations in the Region to take
appropriate steps to promote cooperation between these organizations and the Regional Office in projects
for health development in CCEE/NIS;
<LI>.	URGES Member States to ensure that their bilateral collaborative programmes with CCEE/NIS
actively seek to cooperate with the Regional Office and that their health components are consistent with the
strategy and objectives of the EUROHEALTH programme;
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>	recognizing the needs of CCEE/NIS, to confer with the other Regional Directors and with the
Director-General on the necessity of increasing future allocations of the Organization's budget to regions,
with a view to better serving the health needs of the countries most in need in each of the regions;
<LI>to intensify efforts to mobilize resources, in order to ensure implementation of the EUROHEALTH
programme, recognizing the bilateral collaborative programmes between CCEE, NIS and other Member
States mentioned in operative paragraph 5, as well as multilateral programmes of other international and
regional integrational organizations as collaborative efforts with the EUROHEALTH programme;
<LI>	to take steps to further develop tripartite cooperation within the framework of the EUROHEALTH
programme;
<LI>	to strengthen the work on collecting, analysing and disseminating information on health needs and
health assistance to the CCEE and NIS;
<LI>	to study further possibilities of redistribution in the European regional budget and to report on that
matter, as well as on the EUROHEALTH programme, to the Standing Committee of the Regional
Committee and to the Regional Committee itself at its forty-fourth session.
</OL>
</OL>
<hr>
