<H1 align=center>Resolutions 1992</H1>
<HR>



<H2>Resolution EUR/RC42/R1</H2>
<H2>Reporting on the work of WHO in the European Region
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having reviewed the report of the Regional Director on the work of WHO in the European Region
in 1990-1991 (document EUR/RC42/2);
<LI>	Having considered document EUR/RC42/10 on reporting on the work of WHO in the European
Region, as well as the comments of the Consultative Group on Programme Development thereon;
<LI>	Recognizing the benefit of rationalizing the regional reporting process and bringing it into line
with global practice;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director for his report;
<LI>EXPRESSES its satisfaction with the work accomplished by the Regional Office in the 1990-1991
biennium;
<LI>ASKS the Regional Director to take into account, in the future work of the Regional Office, the
suggestions made during the discussion;
<LI>APPROVES the principle of having only two reporting documents per biennium:  (1) in even-
numbered years, a detailed, factual and evaluative report for the Regional Committee on the work carried
out in the preceding biennium;  (2) in odd-numbered years, a short, illustrated report giving highlights of
major events and developments and aimed at spreading knowledge of the Regional Office for Europe's
mandate and achievements to a wide range of partners, both within and outside the health sector and
particularly at providing information for the general public.
</OL>
<HR>




<H2>Resolution EUR/RC42/R2</H2>
<H2>Action plan for a tobacco-free Europe
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Noting the progress achieved by carrying out the first five-year Action Plan on Tobacco based on
resolution EUR/RC37/R9;
<LI>	Recalling World Health Assembly resolution WHA43.16 on Tobacco or health, which reinforced
the policies adopted in the European concerted action on tobacco;
<LI>	Recalling also resolution EUR/RC41/R8 on Managing the change to a smoke-free Europe, which
requested the Regional Director to develop a second Action Plan to continue the campaign for a tobacco-
free Europe for a further five-year period from 1992 to 1996;
<LI>	Noting document EUR/RC42/9 on the Action Plan for a Tobacco-free Europe;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>RESOLVES to promote stronger Europe-wide action to prevent the health damage caused by tobacco
products;
<LI>DECIDES to strongly support the intentions and the goal of the Action Plan for a Tobacco-free Europe
as set out in document EUR/RC42/9;
<LI>URGES Member States to develop or review their national Action Plans accordingly, including
programmes of education and public information on tobacco and health issues, with active involvement of
the health professions and the media, and to allocate the necessary resources to that end;
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director to call upon intergovernmental and other international, national and
nongovernmental organizations and networks to become partners with WHO in the second Action Plan;
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>to carry out the Action Plan for a Tobacco-free Europe using funds from the regular budget
supplemented by an intensified effort to raise voluntary contributions;
<LI>to make specific mention of progress in carrying out the Action Plan in his reports to the Regional
Committee on the work of the Regional Office, and to submit an evaluation report on its impact to the
Regional Committee at its forty-seventh session in 1997.
</OL>
<LI>REITERATES paragraph 4 of resolution EUR/RC41/R8: "4.  REQUESTS the Regional Director to
call for
<OL>
<LI>		 an international convention banning smoking on international flights;
<LI>		the removal of duty exemptions on tobacco products on international flights and in duty
free shops;"
</OL>
</OL>
<HR>





<H2>Resolution EUR/RC42/R3</H2>
<H2>Technical discussions at future sessions of the Regional Committee
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>	CONFIRMS that the subject of the main technical discussions at its forty-fourth session shall be
"Equity and ethics in health";
<LI>.	REQUESTS the Regional Director to make the necessary arrangements.
</OL>
<HR>





<H2>Resolution EUR/RC42/R4</H2>
<H2>Date and place of regular sessions of the Regional Committee in 1993 and 1994
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having reviewed the decision taken at its forty-first session and taking into account the
recommendation contained in resolution EUR/RC30/R7;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>	CONFIRMS that the forty-third session, by invitation of the Government of Greece, shall be held
in Athens from 6 to 10 September 1993;
<LI>.	DECIDES that the forty-fourth session shall be held at the regional headquarters in Copenhagen
starting on 12 September 1994 for a period not exceeding five days.
</OL>
<HR>






<H2>Resolution EUR/RC42/R5</H2>
<H2>Mobilization for health
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having studied the reports of the Ad Hoc Committee on the Future Orientations of the European
Regional Organization of WHO in a Changing Europe (documents EUR/RC42/4 and
EUR/RC42/Inf.Doc./1) and the proposals and recommendations contained therein;
<LI>	Recalling the discussions at its forty-first session on changing conditions in the European Region
and the increasingly important role in health of major intergovernmental and integrational organizations,
and mindful of the magnitude of the changes in Europe;
<LI>	Taking account of the Ad Hoc Committee's judgement of the potential benefits of, on the one hand,
rapprochement among intergovernmental and integrational organizations with major interests in health in
Europe and, on the other hand, sustaining and reinforcing the trend in the Regional Organization's
programme towards more specificity and selectivity in defining priorities, setting objectives and targeting
activities (documents EUR/RC42/6 and EUR/RC42/11);
<LI>	Conscious of the need to mobilize all interested bodies to address the major health challenges
facing the countries and peoples of the European Region of WHO in accordance with the goals and values
of health for all, and specifically of the regional health for all policy (resolution EUR/RC41/R5);
<LI>	Aware of the associated needs to make essential structural changes in the Regional Organization
due to the significant increase in the number of Member States, to ensure that the Regional Committee
functions purposefully and to the satisfaction of Member States, to ensure a continuing constructive
relationship between the Regional Committee and the Regional Office, and to ensure proper alignment of
priority policy objectives, the structure and budget of the regional programme, and action towards those
objectives by the Regional Office;
<LI>	Convinced that, as a consequence of the present and foreseen changes in Europe, heightened
importance is attached to the deliberations and decisions of the Regional Committee in its policy-making,
supervisory and other roles;
<LI>	Understanding that a particular burden therefore falls on the Chairperson of the Regional
Committee and that the choice and election of the Chairperson of the Regional Committee is therefore a
particularly important task for the Regional Committee;
<LI>	Bearing in mind the initiative taken on the global level, concurrent with the work of the Ad Hoc
Committee, to establish the Working Group of the Executive Board on the WHO Response to Global
Change, and awaiting its conclusions;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>THANKS the Ad Hoc Committee for its work in laying the foundations for a major discussion of this
subject at the forty-second session;
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director and the staff of the Regional Office for their work, for providing
support and valuable background material to the Ad Hoc Committee at all stages of its work and for
expressing their views on the issues of concern;
<LI>	ENDORSES the proposals and recommendations contained in the Ad Hoc Committee's report as
discussed in the Regional Committee;
<LI>	DECIDES to establish the office of Chairperson-elect to be filled by election at each session of the
Regional Committee beginning with the forty-third session, it being understood that the person so elected
will serve as Vice-Chairperson of the session at which that election occurs and then, subject to confirmation
by the Regional Committee, as Chairperson of the following session of the Regional Committee, and to
amend its Rules of Procedure as appropriate;
<LI>	DECIDES to establish a Standing Committee of the Regional Committee as proposed by the Ad
Hoc Committee, to become operative after the forty-third session of the Regional Committee and with a
remit to act for and in support of the Regional Committee in its policy-making, supervisory and other roles,
the full details of its remit and modus operandi to be decided by the Regional Committee at its forty-third
session;
<LI>REQUESTS the Chairperson of the forty-second session of the Regional Committee to take such
immediate steps as he thinks fit, in consultation with representatives of Member States present and with the
Regional Director, to establish and convene an interim Standing Committee of the Regional Committee to
serve until the forty-third session, in order to:
<OL>
<LI>ensure that the momentum generated by the work of the Ad Hoc Committee and by the discussions at
the forty-second session of the Regional Committee is sustained and, as required by the circumstances,
carry out the role of the Standing Committee of the Regional Committee as envisaged by the Ad Hoc
Committee;
<LI>	confer with the Regional Director on the full implications of the recommendations of the Ad Hoc
Committee on the future direction and modus operandi of the Regional Organization, including steps to
secure the effectiveness of the policy-making and supervisory functions of the Regional Committee;
<LI>	review the Rules of Procedure of the Regional Committee and prepare all such proposed
amendments to those Rules as seem in its judgement to be required;
<LI>	develop any further proposals relevant to the proposed remit of the Standing Committee of the
Regional Committee, taking into account any relevant conclusions and recommendations contained in the
report to be submitted by the Executive Board's Working Group on the WHO Response to Global Change
and the issues raised in the Ad Hoc Committee's report;
<LI>	submit its conclusions, recommendations and proposals on all these matters to the Regional
Committee at its forty-third session;
</OL>
<LI>	REQUESTS the Chairperson of the forty-second session of the Regional Committee and the
Regional Director to:
<OL>
<LI>	invite, on behalf of the Regional Committee, the Presidency of the Council of Ministers (of Health)
of the European Communities and the Chair of the European Health Committee of the Council of Europe to
attend a meeting to consider a proposal that representatives of the three organizations form a common
forum, supported by the respective secretariats, and join in due course with others with responsibilities in
the field of health as appropriate, for the development of a common approach towards European
cooperation in the field of health to whose implementation all could contribute;
<LI>	avail themselves of the active support of the interim Standing Committee of the Regional
Committee in seeking this rapprochement;
<LI>	report on this meeting and on any subsequent developments to the Regional Committee at its forty-
third session;
</OL>
<LI>	INVITES Member States to take note of the Ad Hoc Committee's observations on the expectations
and desirable qualities of members of the Standing Committee of the Regional Committee, and to submit
names through the Regional Director to the officers of the forty-second session of the Regional Committee,
by 1 March 1993 at the latest, for consideration as nominations for the Standing Committee of the Regional
Committee;
<LI>	REQUESTS the officers of the forty-second session of the Regional Committee to:
<OL>
<LI>	take the necessary steps through the Regional Director (and in consultation with the interim
Standing Committee) to receive and transmit to the Regional Committee at its forty-third session
nominations for the offices of Chairperson, Chairperson-elect and Rapporteur of that session;
<LI>	propose candidates for election by the Regional Committee at its forty-third session to constitute
the membership of the Standing Committee of the Regional Committee after that session, bearing in mind
the criteria proposed by the Ad Hoc Committee in their report and the desirability, for reasons of continuity
and to make use of their experience, of having up to three members of the interim Standing Committee of
the Regional Committee nominated for a subsequent one-year (1993-94) term of office on the Standing
Committee itself;
</OL>
<LI>	URGES Member States, as members of other intergovernmental and integrational organizations in
Europe and in their other formal bilateral and multilateral intergovernmental contacts, to continue to express
their vigorous support for rapprochement strategies to promote the attainment of health objectives;
<LI>.	REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>as chief executive officer of the Regional Organization, to consider the implications of and to take
action as appropriate on the proposals contained in the report of the Ad Hoc Committee in so far as these
concern:
<OL>
<LI>		 the future of existing advisory bodies, notably the Consultative Group on Programme
Development;
<LI>		 the organizational and managerial structures and staffing of the Regional Office;
</OL>
<LI>	  to report back to the Regional Committee at its forty-third session on action taken and planned.
</OL></OL>

<HR>







<H2>Resolution EUR/RC42/R6</H2>
<H2>Proposed Programme Budget for 1994-1995
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having reviewed the proposed programme budget for the biennium 1994-1995 (document
EUR/RC42/6) and the proposal for an additional regional budget for 1994-1995 (document EUR/RC42/11);
<LI>	Noting that, in the formulation of the programme budget proposals, due consideration has been
given to the Organization's Eighth General Programme of Work, to the regional programme budget policy
(document EUR/RC35/11), to the results of the evaluation of the 1990-1991 programme, to the proposed
programme budget priorities discussed at the forty-first session of the Regional Committee (document
EUR/RC41/5) and to subsequent developments in the Region;
<LI>	Realizing that the new situation in central and eastern European countries has resulted in a major
discrepancy between the need for health assistance to those countries and the programme funds available to
the Regional Office for Europe of WHO;
<LI>	Recalling resolution EUR/RC41/R2, by which the Regional Director was requested to give
priority, in the programme budget proposals for 1994-1995, to continued implementation of the
EUROHEALTH programme;
<LI>	Appreciating the efforts made and the measures being taken by the Organization and the Member
States to supplement the regular budget allocation to the EUROHEALTH programme by means of
extrabudgetary funds;
<LI> 	Bearing in mind the fact that the rapidly evolving situation in the European Region will require:
continuing prioritization, adjustment and adaptation of the programme budget and its structure from now
until the end of the implementation period in 1995;  close cooperation with other international organizations
and between bilateral and multilateral bodies active in the field of health in Europe;  and a transparent
distribution of work within WHO;  and
<LI>	Acutely aware of the role of the Regional Office in international health work in Europe and its
responsibility for assisting the countries of central and eastern Europe with due consideration to the specific
needs of certain countries in southern Europe;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>ENDORSES the proposed programme budget for 1994-1995, which is to be financed with regular
funds and funds from other sources, to the extent that the latter become available;
<LI>RECOMMENDS the inclusion of the European Region's proposed programme budget for 1994-1995
in the Director-General's proposed programme budget for the Organization for 1994-1995;
<LI>CONFIRMS that the Regional Office, in order to play a catalytic role in all countries of central and
eastern Europe in maintaining health and developing health infrastructure as part of the EUROHEALTH
programme, will require at least an additional amount of US$11 million in 1994-1995;
<LI>URGES Member States to make, for this purpose, contributions for the bienna 1992-1993 and 1994-
1995 to the Voluntary Fund for Health Promotion Special Account for the EUROHEALTH programme;
<LI>	DRAWS THE ATTENTION of the Director-General and the Executive Board to the special needs
in the European Region, particularly in central and eastern European countries, which call for a higher
regional allocation from the global budget of the Organization;
<LI>	REQUESTS the Regional Director to mobilize extrabudgetary resources from other organizations
in support of the EUROHEALTH programme;
<LI>	REQUESTS the Regional Director, during preparation and implementation of the regional
programme, to take into account the views expressed by the Regional Committee, and in particular:
<OL>
<LI>		to continue to give high priority to support for health for all in Member States and to
intensify cooperation with countries in central and eastern Europe;
<LI>	to explore all means of strengthening collaboration with other organizations active in the health
field, in particular as regards central and eastern Europe;
<LI>		to continue to ensure a transparent, efficient and economic use of all available resources;
and
</OL>
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director, in order to strengthen the Regional Office's capacity as mentioned
above, to study programme and financing options, including additional or reapportioned appropriations, in
consultation with the interim Standing Committee of the Regional Committee, and to submit a report on this
matter to the Regional Committee at its forty-third session.
</OL>
<HR>





<H2>Resolution EUR/RC42/R7</H2>
<H2>Urgent humanitarian assistance to the war-devastated Republics of Former Yugoslavia
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Strongly reaffirming the principle expressed in the preamble to the European strategy for health for
all (HFA), that peace is a prerequisite for health, and encouraging solidarity between all Member States of
the Region in the spirit of the updated European HFA strategy, particularly its targets 1 and 38;
<LI>	Taking account of the steps being taken by the world community to bring peace in the republics of
former Yugoslavia, and particularly the Programme of Action on Humanitarian Issues agreed at the London
Conference of 26-28 August 1992;
<LI>	Noting that a United Nations Consolidated Inter-Agency Programme of Action has been prepared
and that the appeal launched on 4September 1992 by the Secretary-General of the United Nations includes
a request for contributions to the World Health Organization to meet life-threatening priority needs for
health care, namely for the sum of US$40million over the next seven months;
<LI>	Recalling the coordination role of the office of the United Nations High Commissioner for
Refugees in bringing humanitarian assistance to the affected population;
<LI>	Noting with appreciation that the Regional Director has anticipated the wishes of Member States,
in the spirit of resolution EUR/RC39/R6, to render prompt assistance by establishing a WHO Area Office in
Zagreb to facilitate the health component of international humanitarian aid;
<LI>	Reaffirming as its right and duty the leading role in international health work assigned to WHO
under Article 2 of its Constitution;
<LI>	Affirming, in that connection, that the WHO Regional Office for Europe, in its constitutional
coordinating role for health within the European Region, should act as a mediator and facilitator of health
assistance to populations within that Region;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>THANKS the Director-General of WHO and the Regional Director and other staff, including the staff
in the WHO Area Office in Zagreb, for mobilizing humanitarian assistance and ensuring that this is
delivered despite difficulty and personal danger;
<LI>RECORDS ITS ADMIRATION for the many ordinary citizens in the affected countries who have
offered shelter, food and care to persons in need, irrespective of religion or ethnic origin, and
ACKNOWLEDGES the generous response of Member States in the Region in assisting displaced persons
and refugees;
<LI>EXPRESSES THE VIEW that the burden of meeting the health needs of refugees must be shared by
the whole international community;
<LI>	STRONGLY URGES Member States to earmark contributions to WHO for the health components
of the United Nations Consolidated Inter-Agency Programme of Action and the Appeal for Former
Yugoslavia;
<LI>	REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>in addition to the regular budget, to seek voluntary contributions and give priority within the Regional
Office's resource mobilization efforts to populations in immediate and special need due to the consequences
of war in the war-devastated republics of former Yugoslavia, particularly the Republic of Bosnia and
Herzegovina and the Republic of Croatia;
<LI>	in the context of the United Nations Consolidated Inter-Agency Programme of Action, to develop
a plan for the implementation of this resolution based on objective evaluation of needs and priorities;
<LI>to take steps to prevent further suffering of the affected populations and submit a progress report on
implementation of this resolution at the forty-third session of the Regional Committee.
</OL>
</OL>
<HR>





<H2>Resolution EUR/RC42/R8</H2>
<H2>European Alcohol Action Plan
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Recalling resolutions WHA36.12 and WHA42.20 and document EUR/RC38/11;
<LI>	Recalling also resolution EUR/RC41/R5 on the updating of the Regional targets for health for all,
and in particular target 17;
<LI>	Noting document EUR/RC42/8, which contains proposals for a European Alcohol Action Plan.
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>STRONGLY ENDORSES the European Alcohol Action Plan as set out in document EUR/RC42/8 as
a positive set of guidelines for European Member States to follow;
<LI>URGES Member States to:
<OL>
<LI>	review and, if necessary, reformulate their alcohol policies so as to ensure that their policies are
comprehensive and broadly in line with the principles set out in document EUR/RC42/8;
<LI>	ensure effective implementation of such policies in order to prevent the health risks and
socioeconomic problems often associated with alcohol consumption, recognizing the importance of
multisectoral action and the major role of local communities;
<LI>	develop comprehensive policies and programmes for the prevention and management of alcohol
problems in the context of primary health care;
<LI>	support the adoption of the principles of the European Alcohol Action Plan in other European
organizations that can help make its implementation more effective;
</OL>
<LI>	URGES European intergovernmental and nongovernmental organizations to join forces with the
Regional Office in joint action, maximizing their contribution to a Europe-wide effort towards reducing
alcohol consumption and related health and social problems in Europe;
<LI>	REQUESTS the Regional Director to:
<OL>
<LI>	ensure effective support from the Regional Office and its networks to the European Alcohol Action
Plan, by using funds from WHO's regular budget and increasing the efforts to raise voluntary contributions;
<LI>	cooperate with and assist Member States and intergovernmental and nongovernmental
organizations in their efforts to reduce alcohol-related problems in Europe;
<LI>	report every two years to the Regional Committee on progress in carrying out the Action Plan and
strengthen monitoring and impact analysis of European alcohol consumption during the national and
regional HFA evaluation exercises.
</OL>
</OL>
<hr>
