<H1 align=center>Resolutions 1990</H1>
<HR>


<H2>Resolution EUR/RC40/R1</H2>
<H2>Annual report of the Regional Director
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having reviewed the reports on the work of WHO in the European Region in 1989 and the first six
months of 1990;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director for his reports;
<LI>EXPRESSES its satisfaction with the work accomplished by the Regional Office in 1989 and during
the first six months of 1990;
<LI>ASKS the Regional Director to take into account the suggestions made during the discussion in the
future work of the Regional Office.
</OL>
<HR>


<H2>Resolution EUR/RC40/R2</H2>
<H2>Expanded programme on immunization - progress report
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Recalling resolution EUR/RC34/R5 endorsing the regional HFA targets, and more specifically
target 5, according to which there should be no indigenous measles, poliomyelitis, neonatal tetanus,
congenital rubella, diphtheria, congenital syphilis or indigenous malaria in the Region by the year 2000;
<LI>	Reaffirming resolution EUR/RC35/R5 which urges Member States to accelerate the
implementation of existing immunization programmes, to increase vaccination coverage to meet regional
target 5 and to place more emphasis on the evaluation of the expanded programme on immunization;
<LI>	Bearing in mind the plan of action for the eradication of poliomyelitis from the European Region,
contained in document EUR/RC39/9 and endorsed by the Regional Committee at its thirty-ninth session in
support of resolution WHA41.28 pledging the global eradication of poliomyelitis by the year 2000;
<LI>	Referring to resolution WHA42.32 urging Member States to eliminate neonatal tetanus from the
world by 1995;
<LI>	Noting with satisfaction the efforts made by the Regional Director since 1984 to develop the
regional expanded programme on immunization, which has already resulted in a further decrease in the
incidence of diphtheria, tetanus, neonatal tetanus, pulmonary tuberculosis and particularly poliomyelitis;
<LI>	Expressing its concern about continuing outbreaks of poliomyelitis, diphtheria, measles, rubella,
and viral hepatitis in some Member States, due to deficiencies in immunity of the population;
<LI>	Having considered the progress report on the expanded programme on immunization (document
EUR/RC40/12);
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director for the progress report;
<LI>URGES all Member States to review and strengthen national and subnational endeavours to improve
immunization to make it effective enough not only to attain the goals of regional HFA target 5 but also to
control other communicable diseases preventable by immunization;
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>	  to supplement the funds available to the Regional Office by actively seeking extrabudgetary
resources for further development of the programme related to regional HFA target5;
<LI>	  to cooperate closely with UNICEF;
<LI>	  to report on progress to the Regional Committee at regular intervals.
</OL>
</OL>
<HR>


<H2>Resolution EUR/RC40/R3</H2>
<H2>Mechanicms and procedure for the selection of the Regional Director for Europe
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Conscious of the vital role of the Regional Director in the work of WHO in the European Region
and of the need to establish a clear procedure to ensure the suitability of candidates in terms of their
personal and technical competence for the post;
<LI>	Bearing in mind the discussions on the subject which took place at the thirty-seventh and thirty-
eighth sessions of the Regional Committee;
<LI>	Having reviewed document EUR/RC40/4 on the mechanisms and procedure for selection of the
Regional Director for Europe, the evaluation of the experimental phase and the Consultative Group on
Programme Development's comments thereon (document EUR/RC40/7);
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>	APPROVES the proposals set out in document EUR/RC40/4 regarding criteria for candidates for
the post of Regional Director and the selection process;
<LI>	AMENDS Rules 5 and 47 of the Rules of Procedure of the Regional Committee for Europe as
follows.
</OL>
<H3>RULES OF PROCEDURE OF THE REGIONAL
COMMITTEE FOR EUROPE</H3>
<I><B>Rule 5</B></I><P><B><I>
</I></B>	At the end of the text,
<I>add</I>:<P>
	"In the event that the post of Regional Director unexpectedly falls vacant, the Director-General
may, in consultation with the Chairman, convene the Committee for the purpose of establishing a Regional
Search Group and taking related decisions in accordance with Rule 47."<P>
<I><B>Rule 47</B></I><P><B><I>
</I><I></B>New paragraph</I><P><I>
</I>	At the beginning of the text, <I>insert</I> a new paragraph as follows:<P>
	"1.	At its session preceding the one at
which a person is due to be nominated as Regional Director, the Committee shall appoint a Regional Search
Group to make a preliminary evaluation of candidates for nomination in the light of the criteria specified by
the Committee and to perform related functions as set out in this Rule."<P>
<I>Paragraph 1</I><P><I>
</I>	In the first line, <I>replace</I> the figure "1" by "2" and the words "six months" by "eleven
months".<P>
<I>Paragraph 2</I><P><I>
</I>	<I>Replace</I> the figure "2" in the first line by "3" and the words "twelve weeks" in the fifth
line by "seven months" and <I>add</I> the following sentences at the end of the paragraph:<P>
	"This time limit may be extended by the Chairman of the Committee on the proposal of the
Regional Search Group.  Any such extension shall be communicated by the Chairperson of the Regional
Search Group to the Director-General, who shall promptly inform the Member States of the Region."<P>
<I>Paragraph 3</I><P><I>
</I>	In the first line, <U>replace</U> the figure "3" by "4" and in the second line, after the words "so
requested", <U>insert</U> "within the time limit referred to in paragraph3".<P>
<I>New paragraph</I><P><I>
</I>	<I>Insert</I> a new paragraph 5 as follows:<P>
	"5.	Not later than two weeks after the
expiration of the time limit referred to in paragraph3, the Director-General shall transmit a list of names
and all particulars of candidates received to the Chairperson of the Regional Search Group."<P>
<I>Paragraph 4</I><P><I>
</I>	<I>Replace</I> the figure "4" in the first line by "6".  At the end of the paragraph,
<U>insert</U> the following phrase:<P>
	"... as well as to the Chairperson of the Regional Search Group."<P>
<I>New paragraph</I><P><I>
</I>	<I>Insert</I> a new paragraph 7 as follows:<P>
	"7.	At the same time, the Chairperson of
the Regional Search Group shall send, under confidential cover, the evaluation report of the Search Group
to the Chairman of the Committee, to each Member State of the Region for the attention of its chief
representative designated to attend the Committee's next session, and to the Director-General."<P>
<I>Paragraph 5</I><P><I>
</I>	For the existing text, <I>substitute</I>:<P>
	"8.	If within the prescribed time limit no
proposals have been received in accordance with paragraph 3, and no request has been made by a person
holding office as Regional Director for the Region as described in paragraph 4, or if in the opinion of the
Regional Search Group the candidatures submitted did not offer an adequate choice for the Committee, the
Regional Search Group shall propose the extension of the time limit in accordance with paragraph3.  It
shall take such action as it considers appropriate to identify potential candidates and report to the Member
States of the Region on the results of such action.  The Regional Search Group may also propose the name
or names of one or more persons for nomination as Regional Director in accordance with the procedure set
out in paragraph3."<P>
<I>Paragraph 6</I><P><I>
</I>	For the existing text, <I>substitute</I>:<P>
	"9.	In the event that the post of Regional
Director unexpectedly falls vacant, the Director-General shall:<P>
		(a)  designate a person to act as
Regional Director until the appointment of a new incumbent;<P>
		(b)  decide, in consultation with the
Chairman, whether a special meeting of the Committee should be convened as set out in Rule 5."<P>
<I>Paragraphs 7-10</I><P><I>
</I>	<I>Renumber</I> paragraphs 7, 8, 9 and 10 as paragraphs 10, 11, 12 and 13 respectively.<P>
<HR>



<H2>Resolution EUR/RC40/R4</H2>
<H2>Technical discussions at future sessions of the Regional Committee
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>CONFIRMS that the subject of the main technical discussions at its forty-second session shall be
"Health care financing";
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director to make the necessary arrangements.
</OL>
<HR>



<H2>Resolution EUR/RC40/R5</H2>
<H2>Evaluation of the strategy for health for all in 1990-1991
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Recalling resolution WHA39.7, which led to the preparation of the second report on monitoring
progress in the implementation of strategies for health for all;
<LI>	Bearing in mind resolution WHA41.27, which stresses the use and development of epidemiology
in support of health for all strategies;
<LI>	Bearing in mind resolution WHA42.2, which, <U>inter alia</U>, urges the Member States to
continue to monitor progress and to carry out the second evaluation  of their strategies in time for the 1992
world health situation report and the regional committees to support the implementation of the second
evaluation of the regional strategies in 1991;
<LI>	Having considered:
<OL>
<LI>the regional targets in support of the regional strategy for health for all a);
<LI>the proposed HFA indicators and evaluation framework for the European Region of WHO (1990-
1991);
<LI>the monitoring of the strategy for health for all by the year 2000 b);  and
<LI>the report of the Consultative Group on Programme Development (EUR/RC40/7);
</OL>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director, the advisory groups and the experts involved in the preparation of
those documents for their valuable contributions;
<LI>ENDORSES, for application according to the particular circumstances of individual Member States,
the HFA indicators and evaluation framework for the European Region of WHO (1990-1991), the
procedure for evaluating progress towards HFA and proposed future developments (EUR/RC40/9);
<LI>URGES Member States:
<OL>
<LI>	  when reporting to the Regional Director, to provide all the necessary information on progress
and effectiveness in implementing their strategies for health for all, including data related to the global and
regional indicators as reflected in the above document;
<LI>	  to seek Regional Office cooperation as and when required for these purposes;
</OL>
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>to transmit these documents, adapted where necessary to take account of constitutional matters in
particular Member States, together with the minutes of the Regional Committee, to the Director-General as
a European regional contribution to the attainment of the global target of health for all;
<LI>to report to the Regional Committee in accordance with the proposed procedure for evaluation.
</OL>
</UL>
a) <I>Targets for health for all</I>. Copenhagen, WHO Regional Office for Europe, 1985
(European Health for All Series, No. 1).<P>
	b) <I>Monitoring of the strategy for health for all by the year 2000: Part 1: The situation
in the European Region 1987/1988</I>. Copenhagen, WHO Regional Office for Europe,
1989.<P>
<HR>



<H2>Resolution EUR/RC40/R6</H2>
<H2>European HFA information strategy
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having considered document EUR/RC40/11 on information strategy for HFA;
<LI>	Recognizing the need to improve information support for HFA policy formulation, implementation
and evaluation;
<LI>	Acknowledging that the main improvements will have to be made in the Member States;
<LI>	Recognizing that while information is a resource for the achievement of HFA, resources are also
required for its production and effective use;
<LI>	Taking into account the comments made by the Regional Committee;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>ENDORSES the principles of the European HFA information policy and strategy as laid down in the
document presented;
<LI>	CALLS UPON Member States who have not already done so to:
<OL>
<LI>reassess their capacity for information support in the light of the new demands made by the HFA
policy;
<LI>strengthen their technical and managerial capacity in health information, <U>inter alia</U> by means
of human resources development, and develop coordinated health information systems;
<LI>consider the establishment of national WHO documentation centres and their incorporation into a
coordinated expert information network of WHO collaborating centres;
<LI>improve the monitoring of progress towards HFA;
</OL>
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director to:
<OL>
<LI>support the development of health information systems in the Member States;
<LI>support the development of decentralized information centres and databases in WHO collaborating
centres;
<LI>strengthen coordination and cooperation with intergovernmental and nongovernmental organizations;
<LI>develop further the Regional Office's role as a European health information centre;
<LI>support implementation of the European HFA information policy and strategy through updating of
target 35 and through future programme budgets;
<LI>report regularly to the Regional Committee on progress made.
</OL>
</OL>
<HR>



<H2>Resolution EUR/RC40/R7</H2>
<H2>Cooperation with countries of central nad eastern Europe
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having studied the report submitted by the Regional Director (EUR/RC40/Inf.Doc./2);
<LI>	Mindful of the continuing health problems which still exist in certain Member States yet noting
with grave concern the gap in health status between Member States of central and eastern Europe and many
other parts of the Region and the possible rapid further deterioration of the situation in the short term;
<LI>	Aware of the fact that this situation can only be corrected gradually and on the basis of lasting
international solidarity;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>THANKS the Regional Director for his report;
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director to intensify cooperation in health with central and eastern
European countries through a programme in the form of a five-year plan of action to be supported from
regular and extrabudgetary resources;
<LI>ENCOURAGES the countries concerned to redeploy their own resources towards implementation of
health reforms, according to their perceived needs and in line with the European health for all strategy and
targets, striking a balance between immediate needs and longer-term goals;
<LI>URGES Member States, intergovernmental bodies, nongovernmental organizations, private
foundations and corporations to support the new programme and intensify their assistance to the countries
concerned, availing themselves of WHO's coordinating function;
<LI>DECIDES to establish an Advisory Subcommittee of the Regional Committee (whose members shall
be appointed by the officers of the fortieth session of the Regional Committee in such a manner as to ensure
broad representation of Member States and to include the Member States concerned) to advise the Regional
Director whenever necessary on all aspects of the programme, including the management and monitoring of
its implementation, and to report on progress to the Regional Committee;
<LI>INVITES the Chairperson (or one of the Vice-Chairpersons designated by him/her) of the Regional
Committee to chair the Advisory Subcommittee;
<LI>FURTHER REQUESTS the Regional Director:
<OL>
<LI>to develop urgently a programme as mentioned above, distinguishing between immediate and long-
term action, and to submit this, in the first instance, to the Advisory Subcommittee;
<LI>to reallocate resources in the 1990-1991 budget up to US $1 million, and to make provision for US $2
million from the 1992-1993 programme budget for the implementation of the action plan;
<LI>	to intensify efforts to mobilize extrabudgetary resources;
<LI>	in consultation with the Advisory Subcommittee to explore with the Director-General ways and
means by which the support of headquarters technical and other resources to the regional programme can be
strengthened.
</OL>
</OL>
<HR>



<H2>Resolution EUR/RC40/R8</H2>
<H2>Proposed Programme Budget for 1992-1993
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having reviewed in detail the proposed programme budget for the biennium 1992-1993 and noted
the modified presentation of the programme budget document (document EUR/RC40/8);
<LI>	Noting that, in the formulation of the proposals, due consideration has been given to the
Organization's Eighth General Programme of Work covering the period 1990-1995, to the regional
programme budget policy (document EUR/RC35/11), to the results of the evaluation of the 1988-1989
programme, to the priorities endorsed by Member States at the thirty-ninth session of the Regional
Committee (document EUR/RC39/5) and to the comments given by Member States in their replies to the
consultation document on selected programme budget issues for 1992-1993;
<LI>	Having considered the comments made by the Consultative Group on Programme Development;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>REQUESTS the Regional Director, during implementation of the programme, to take into account the
views expressed by the Regional Committee, and in particular:
<OL>
<LI>	to continue to give high priority to outputs and objectives in support of health for all, and where
necessary to make corresponding adjustments in the budgetary allocations;
<LI>	to make such redeployments in the proposed programme budget for 1992-1993 as are necessary to
give effect to the provisions of the resolution on cooperation with countries of central and eastern Europe;
<LI>	to ensure the most efficient and economic use of all available resources;
</OL>
<LI>ENDORSES, on this basis, the proposed programme budget for 1992-1993, which is to be financed
with regular funds and funds from other sources, to the extent that the latter become available;
<LI>RECOMMENDS, on the same basis, its inclusion in the Director-General's proposed programme
budget for the Organization for 1992-1993.
</OL>
<HR>


<H2>Resolution EUR/RC40/R9</H2>
<H2>Reports of the Regional Director and of the Regional Committee
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having considered document EUR/RC40/10 on the reports of the Regional Director and of the
Regional Committee as well as the comments of the Consultative Group on Programme Development
thereon;
<LI>	Recognizing also that the annual report of the Regional Director on the work of WHO in the
European Region cannot be both a detailed factual report and a promotional tool;
<LI>	Aware of the development by the Regional Office of a comprehensive communications promotion
policy;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>ENDORSES the proposal to replace the publication containing the annual report of the Regional
Director on the work of WHO in the European Region by two documents:  (1)  an annual detailed, factual
and evaluative report on the activities of the Regional Office for the Regional Committee and (2)  an annual
illustrated booklet intended for general public information;
<LI>WELCOMES the suggestion to improve the information flow between Member States and the
Regional Office through a periodic newsletter;
<LI>DECIDES - notwithstanding Rule 18 of the Rules of Procedures of the Regional Committee - to
discontinue, on a two-year trial basis, the production of the written minutes of meetings of the Regional
Committee and to replace them by sound recordings;  recordings of the whole or part of the session shall be
made available to Member States on request in the original language of the speakers and/or the
interpretation into any of the four working languages of the Region;  transcripts of specific parts of sessions
shall likewise be made available on request.
</OL>
<HR>



<H2>Resolution EUR/RC40/R10</H2>
<H2>Date and place of regular sessions of the Regional Committee in 1991 and 1992
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>	The Regional Committee,
<LI>	Having reviewed the decision taken at its thirty-ninth session and taking into account the
recommendation contained in resolution EUR/RC30/R7;
</UL>
<OL>
<LI>CONFIRMS that the forty-first session shall be held in Lisbon, Portugal, from 10 to 14 September
1991;
<LI>DECIDES that the forty-second session shall be convened at the regional headquarters in Copenhagen
in September/October 1992 for a period not exceeding six days.
</OL>
